Section 1:
1 L.D. 1840
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 723, L.D. 1840, “An Act to Amend the
10 Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §2422-A, as repealed and replaced by PL 2023, c. 365, §1, is
14 amended by amending the section headnote to read:
15 §2422-A. Administration and enforcement; rulemaking; attestations
16 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §2422-A, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
17 3. Attestations for registration or renewal. Except when explicitly authorized or
18 directed under this chapter, the office may not require a registrant to make any attestations
19 on any forms or documents regarding any conduct authorized pursuant to this chapter or
20 the rules adopted pursuant to this chapter in order to comply with the registration or renewal
21 requirements of this chapter. This subsection may not be construed to prohibit such
22 attestations on any forms or documents subject to any proceedings pursuant to section
23 2430-I, subsection 9 or attestations on any forms or documents accompanied by a signature
24 that the information contained within the form or document is accurate or complete.
25 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §2423-A, sub-§2, ¶O, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 452, §4 and
26 amended by PL 2021, c. 669, §5, is further amended to read:
27 O. Transport Sell, offer to sell, furnish or transport cannabis plants or harvested
28 cannabis for authorized conduct in accordance with this chapter on the property or
29 premises owned, leased or rented by the caregiver, subject to the terms of any lease or
30 rental agreement; at trade shows or other industry-related events regarding cannabis
31 for medical use; or through delivery to or private arrangement with a qualifying patient
32 or registrant as long as the delivery or private arrangement occurs on property or at
33 premises owned, leased or rented, subject to the terms of any lease or rental agreement,
34 by the caregiver, qualifying patient or registrant or on public property that is not
35 designated as a safe zone by a municipality pursuant to Title 30-A, section 3253 or in
Page 1 - 132LR0989(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 723, L.D. 1840
316 any other public space where the sale, furnishing or transport of cannabis plants or
327 harvested cannabis is prohibited in law;
3 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §2430-N, sub-§8, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 365, §25, is amended
4 to read:
5 8. Sales Gross sales; sales tax revenue. The gross sales of cannabis for medical use
6 for the current and prior fiscal years and the sales tax revenue from the sale of cannabis for
7 medical use deposited into the General Fund for the current and prior fiscal years.
8 Sec. 5. Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
9 Cannabis Policy; medical cannabis research grant program rulemaking. On
10 or before January 9, 2026, the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office
11 of Cannabis Policy shall provisionally adopt and submit for legislative review rules
12 necessary to implement the medical cannabis research grant program in accordance with
13 the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section 2430, subsection 5. Rules adopted by the
14 office pursuant to this section are major substantive rules as defined in Title 5, chapter 375,
15 subchapter 2-A.
16 Sec. 6. Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
17 Cannabis Policy; availability of medical use of cannabis registration and
18 renewal forms. The Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
19 Cannabis Policy shall as expeditiously as possible make available on the office's publicly
20 accessible website all registration and renewal forms in their entirety as a portable
21 document file or similar file format that does not require the use of independent software,
22 hardware or operating systems. The office shall also make available registration and
23 renewal forms in their entirety in paper form available at the office. This section does not
24 preclude the office from also offering registration and renewal forms through an online
25 registration portal or similar system.
26 Sec. 7. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
27 allocations are made.
28 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
29 Medical Use of Cannabis Fund Z265
30 Initiative: Provides funding for one Office Specialist I position, one OCP Chief Licensing
31 Investigator position and 8 OCP Licensing Analyst positions and associated All Other
32 costs.
33 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
34 POSITIONS - LEGISLATIVE COUNT 10.000 10.000
35 Personal Services $1,075,405 $1,162,757
36 All Other $82,316 $82,316
37 __________ __________
38 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $1,157,721 $1,245,073
3393 '
40 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
41 number to read consecutively.
Page 2 - 132LR0989(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 723, L.D. 1840
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment makes the following changes to the
33 Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act.
4 1. It provides that, except when explicitly authorized or directed under the Maine
5 Medical Use of Cannabis Act, the Department of Administrative and Financial Services,
6 Office of Cannabis Policy may not require a registrant to make any attestations on any
7 forms or documents regarding any conduct authorized pursuant to the Maine Medical Use
8 of Cannabis Act or the rules adopted pursuant to the Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act,
9 except as may be required under the Maine Administrative Procedure Act regarding
10 administrative penalties.
11 2. It provides that a caregiver is authorized to sell, offer to sell, furnish or transport
12 cannabis plants or harvested cannabis on property or premises owned, leased or rented,
13 subject to the terms of any lease or rental agreement, by the caregiver; at trade shows or
14 other industry-related events regarding cannabis for medical use; or through delivery to or
15 private arrangement with a qualifying patient or registrant as long as the delivery or private
16 arrangement occurs on property or at premises owned, leased or rented by the caregiver,
17 subject to the terms of any lease or rental agreement qualifying patient or registrant or on
18 public property that is not designated as a safe zone by a municipality or in any other public
19 space where the sale, furnishing or transport of cannabis plants or harvested cannabis is
20 prohibited by law.
21 3. It provides that the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, in its
22 annual report to the Legislature regarding the medical use of cannabis, must include
23 information regarding the gross sales of cannabis for medical use for the current and prior
24 fiscal years.
25 4. It directs the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
26 Cannabis Policy, on or before January 9, 2026, to provisionally adopt and submit for
27 legislative review major substantive rules necessary to implement the medical cannabis
28 research grant program in accordance with the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section
29 2430, subsection 5.
30 5. It directs the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
31 Cannabis Policy to, as expeditiously as possible, make available on the office's publicly
32 accessible website all registration and renewal forms in their entirety as a portable
33 document file or similar file format that does not require the use of independent software,
34 hardware or operating systems. It also directs the office to make those forms available at
35 the office on paper. It does not prohibit the office from also offering registration and
36 renewal forms through an online registration portal or similar system.
3377 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3388 (See attached)
