COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 723, L.D. 1840
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment makes the following changes to the
33 Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act.
4 1. It provides that, except when explicitly authorized or directed under the Maine
5 Medical Use of Cannabis Act, the Department of Administrative and Financial Services,
6 Office of Cannabis Policy may not require a registrant to make any attestations on any
7 forms or documents regarding any conduct authorized pursuant to the Maine Medical Use
8 of Cannabis Act or the rules adopted pursuant to the Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act,
9 except as may be required under the Maine Administrative Procedure Act regarding
10 administrative penalties.
11 2. It provides that a caregiver is authorized to sell, offer to sell, furnish or transport
12 cannabis plants or harvested cannabis on property or premises owned, leased or rented,
13 subject to the terms of any lease or rental agreement, by the caregiver; at trade shows or
14 other industry-related events regarding cannabis for medical use; or through delivery to or
15 private arrangement with a qualifying patient or registrant as long as the delivery or private
16 arrangement occurs on property or at premises owned, leased or rented by the caregiver,
17 subject to the terms of any lease or rental agreement qualifying patient or registrant or on
18 public property that is not designated as a safe zone by a municipality or in any other public
19 space where the sale, furnishing or transport of cannabis plants or harvested cannabis is
20 prohibited by law.
21 3. It provides that the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, in its
22 annual report to the Legislature regarding the medical use of cannabis, must include
23 information regarding the gross sales of cannabis for medical use for the current and prior
24 fiscal years.
25 4. It directs the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
26 Cannabis Policy, on or before January 9, 2026, to provisionally adopt and submit for
27 legislative review major substantive rules necessary to implement the medical cannabis
28 research grant program in accordance with the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 22, section
29 2430, subsection 5.
30 5. It directs the Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of
31 Cannabis Policy to, as expeditiously as possible, make available on the office's publicly
32 accessible website all registration and renewal forms in their entirety as a portable
33 document file or similar file format that does not require the use of independent software,
34 hardware or operating systems. It also directs the office to make those forms available at
35 the office on paper. It does not prohibit the office from also offering registration and
36 renewal forms through an online registration portal or similar system.
